107
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,260
[Origin]

108
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,160
Yang.

109
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,280
Mr. Song, what brings you here?

110
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,480
Do you know where Xi is?

111
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,640
I need to see her urgently.

112
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,520
I haven't been able to reach her.

113
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,160
This afternoon she went with He Jiayang

114
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,920
and Qian to the hospital to see He Zheng.

115
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,120
She might not have her phone with her.

116
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,080
How badly was He Zheng hurt?

117
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,680
Jiayang said this afternoon it wasn't serious.

118
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,120
They're keeping him there

119
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,280
for observation, just in case.

120
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,360
Otherwise, he'd be discharged already.

121
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,680
Is it something urgent?

122
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:04,480
Yes. I'm almost certain now

123
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,360
this incident was no accident.

124
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,760
It was deliberately staged.

125
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,360
That's why I need to see her ASAP,

126
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,520
to figure out our next move.

127
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:14,760
An evil queen preying on an innocent boy.

128
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,120
If word gets out,

129
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,320
it'll cause quite a stir.

130
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,320
So what do we do?

131
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,640
Then I'll leave.

132
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,480
You think you can come and go

133
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,480
whenever you want?

134
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,560
Not that easy.

135
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,160
You're not getting out of this.

136
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,640
So, what do you want me to do?

137
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,760
Grab my phone.

138
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,080
[Yang]

139
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,120
Who is it?

140
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,200
Yang.

141
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,560
Hey, Yang. What's up?

142
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,040
Hello?

143
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,080
Chu, why didn't you answer?

144
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,080
Mr. Song's been looking for you.

145
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,280
I was tied up just now.

146
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:56,680
I didn't hear my phone.

147
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,080
Can you come to the office?

148
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,680
Right now? At this hour?

149
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,040
Here.

150
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:04,960
Where are you?

151
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:05,960
You didn't answer my calls.

152
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,880
You didn't reply either.

153
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,360
Do you know how worried I was?

154
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,280
Listen carefully.

155
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,280
This incident isn't that simple.

156
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,520
Someone set it up.

157
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:15,680
You mean someone's targeting us?

158
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:18,080
Yes. They're coming after us.

159
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,440
What was that noise?

160
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,360
I was swatting a mosquito.

161
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,560
I haven't been sleeping well lately.

162
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,640
And this mosquito just won't stop.

163
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:28,880
It keeps buzzing. Super annoying!

164
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:35,520
Alright. You've been through a lot.

165
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,240
It's getting late.

166
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,280
Get some rest.

167
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,160
Let's meet at the office tomorrow morning.

168
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:43,160
Okay. See you tomorrow.

169
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,360
Did you do that on purpose?

170
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,480
What, are you jealous?

171
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,640
I have no idea what you're talking about.

172
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,680
You really don't understand?

173
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,080
No clue at all.

174
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,040
You little punk.

175
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,560
Again?

176
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,200
Why not?

177
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,080
Is it...

178
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,080
bad?

179
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:26,760
Not at all.

180
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,440
It's totally my kind of food.

181
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,440
I really love it.

182
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,240
It's so good.

183
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:34,880
Alright, I'll cook again tomorrow.

184
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,360
You're cooking again tomorrow?

185
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,680
Wouldn't that be too tiring?

186
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,680
It's not tiring.

187
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:49,920
Then that's great.

188
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,960
Sure, I love it.

189
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,960
If you like it, have more.

190
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:16,140
[Mr. Song]

191
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:18,960
One second.

192
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,240
Mr. Song's calling me.

193
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,440
Mr. Song?

194
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,880
Hello, Mr. Song.

195
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,880
He Jiayang, are you at the hospital?

196
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,480
Yeah, I am.

197
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,680
How's He Zheng doing?

198
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,200
He Zheng?

199
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,520
He's been discharged.

200
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,680
He Zheng's been discharged?

201
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:36,760
